# Cypress Testing Rules

Rules for AI agents writing and evaluating Cypress tests in the frontend/v2 directory.

## Sub-Rules
This rule delegates to focused sub-rules. Consult these for detailed standards:

*   **Structure & Naming**: @testing/frontend/cypress.structure.mdc
    *   File patterns (`.unit.cy.ts`, `.cy.js`)
    *   Directory structure
    *   Test hierarchy

*   **Selectors & Commands**: @testing/frontend/cypress.selectors.mdc
    *   `data-testid` priority
    *   Custom commands (`cy.getByTestId`)
    *   Page Objects

*   **Mocking & Fixtures**: @testing/frontend/cypress.mocking.mdc
    *   `cy.intercept` patterns
    *   GraphQL mocking
    *   Typed fixtures (Shared Fixtures Strategy)

*   **Patterns & Anti-Patterns**: @testing/frontend/cypress.patterns.mdc
    *   Assertions
    *   Visibility issues (`{ force: true }`)
    *   Common mistakes (Arbitrary waits)

*   **Zustand Store Testing**: @testing/frontend/cypress.zustand.mdc
    *   Setting state with `setState()`
    *   Asserting state after interactions (`cy.then`)
    *   Why `cy.spy`/`cy.stub` must not be used on store methods

*   **Kestrix Survey (`front_end/v2/kestrix_survey/`)**: @front_end/.cursor/rules/testing/kestrix_survey/cypress-overview.mdc
    *   Component vs E2E decision framework and `cy.mount`-first atom testing
    *   Delegates to @front_end/.cursor/rules/testing/kestrix_survey/cypress-component.mdc, @front_end/.cursor/rules/testing/kestrix_survey/cypress-e2e.mdc, @front_end/.cursor/rules/testing/kestrix_survey/cypress-quality.mdc

## Checklist Summary
Before submitting test code, verify:
- [ ] **Structure**: Tests are idempotent (Arrange-Act-Assert) and use `beforeEach()`
- [ ] **Selectors**: Used `data-testid` via `cy.getByTestId` or centralised constants
- [ ] **Mocking**: All API/GraphQL calls mocked with `cy.intercept`
- [ ] **Timing**: No `cy.wait(ms)`; specific aliases waited (`@createItem`)
- [ ] **Fixtures**: Typed fixtures + `cleanup()` (`shared/fixtures/` and/or app `tests/fixtures/` as used by the package)
- [ ] **Zustand**: Used `cy.then()` for post-interaction state assertions; no `cy.spy`/`cy.stub` on store methods
- [ ] **Environment**: Stubbed globals and used `Cypress.env()`
